  "response": "The Alma Mater Society (AMS) is typically the student government organization at the University of British Columbia (UBC) in Vancouver, Canada. It represents and serves the undergraduate student body, providing various services, advocacy, and support for students. The AMS is responsible for:\n\n1. Student representation and advocacy\n2. Running student services and businesses\n3. Organizing campus events\n4. Managing student clubs and organizations\n5. Providing support for student welfare and rights\n\nWhile this description specifically refers to UBC's AMS, other universities may have similar student government organizations that also use the term \"Alma Mater Society.\"",
